cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.NA 

The paper deals with image reconstruction using a deep learning approach and iterative algorithms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves learning non-linear annihilation relations in Fourier space, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IT (Information Theory). The use of deep learning to reduce computational complexity makes it relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves optimization techniques, which could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the use of iterative algorithms and optimization techniques suggests that it could belong to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
